{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 22,
  "title": "第二十二章（執一）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "曲則全。枉則正。洼則盈。敝則新。少則得。多則惑。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人執一，以為天下牧。"
    },
    {
      "text": "不自視故明。不自見故彰。不自伐故有功。弗矜故能長。"
    },
    {
      "text": "夫唯不爭，故莫能與之爭。古之所謂曲全者，幾語才，誠全歸之。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "枉，屈己而伸人，久久自得直也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "地窪下，水流之；人謙下，德歸之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "自受弊薄，後己先人，天下敬之，久久自新也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 21
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "自受取少則得多也，天道祐謙，神明託虛。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 26
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "財多者，惑於所守，學多者，惑於所聞。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "抱，守也。式，法也。聖人守一，乃知萬事，故能為天下法式也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人不以其目視千里之外也，乃因天下之目以視，故能明達也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人不自以為是而非人，故能彰顯於世。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 22,
          "end": 23
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "伐，取也。聖人德化流行，不自取其美，故有功於天下。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "矜，大也。聖人不自貴大，故能久不危。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "此言天下賢與不肖，無能與不爭者爭也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 29,
          "end": 29
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "傳古言，曲從則全身，此言非虛妄也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-13",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 29,
          "end": 29
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "誠，實也。能行曲從者，實其肌體，歸之於父母，無有傷害也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不自是則其是彰也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不自伐則其功有也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不自矜則其德長也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 21
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "自然之道亦猶樹也，轉多轉遠其根，轉少轉得其本。多則遠其真，故曰惑也；少則得其本，故曰得也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一，少之極也。式，猶則之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
